org.livingdoc.api.documents

Annotation Type ExecutableDocument


  • @Testable
 @Target
 @Retention
public ExecutableDocument

    This annotation is used to mark a class as an executable document. The Living Doc engine looks for this annotation to find the documents that should be executed. The annotated class can contain annotationclass DecisionTableFixture and annotationclass ScenarioFixtures. The executed contents are referenced as a parameter of the annotation. An ExecutableDocument can be grouped by using the annotationclass Group annotation. An ExecutableDocument can be disabled by using the annotationclass Disabled annotation.

    See Also:
    annotationclass DecisionTableFixture, annotationclass ScenarioFixture, annotationclass Group, annotationclass Disabled
